exercise.p:
Check the presentation for errors. If you find one, circle it and describe the mistake in words. 

	\begin{aligned}
		\frac{3}{4} \cdot \frac{4}{3} \amp = \frac{\cancel{3}}{\cancel{4}} \cdot \frac{\cancel{4}}{\cancel{3}} \amp \eqnspacer \amp \text{Reduce} \\
		\amp = 0 
	\end{aligned}

Check the presentation for errors. If you find one, circle it and describe the mistake in words. 

	\begin{aligned}
		\frac{5}{14} \cdot \frac{7}{15} \amp = \frac{5}{2 \cdot 7} \cdot \frac{7}{3 \cdot 5} \amp \eqnspacer \amp \text{Identify common factors} \\
		\amp = \frac{\cancel{5}}{2 \cdot \cancel{7}} \cdot \frac{\cancel{7}}{3 \cdot \cancel{5}} \amp \amp \text{Reduce} \\
		\amp = 6 
	\end{aligned}
